# Code Style — Biome Enforced

All code in this project is formatted and linted by Biome. Follow these conventions so output is clean on first pass.

## Formatting

- **Indent**: 2 spaces (no tabs)
- **Quotes**: single quotes for JS/TS, double quotes for JSX attributes
- **Semicolons**: always
- **Trailing commas**: everywhere (function params, objects, arrays, etc.)
- **Line width**: 100 characters max
- **Line endings**: LF only
- **Arrow functions**: always wrap params in parentheses — `(x) => x`, not `x => x`
- **Object quote properties**: only when needed

## Imports

- Auto-sorted by Biome (organize imports enabled)
- Use `import type { Foo }` when importing only types — never import a type as a value
- Use `node:` protocol for Node.js built-ins — `import { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises'`, not `'fs/promises'`
- Remove unused imports (error)

## Linter Rules (errors that MUST be followed)

- **No unused variables or imports** — remove them, don't leave dead code
- **No `any`** — use `unknown`, generics, or proper types. Never `as any` or `: any`
- **No `console.*`** — use the project logger (pino). Exception: test files
- **Use block statements** — always use braces for `if`/`else`/`for`/`while`. No single-line bodies
- **No non-null assertions** — avoid `foo!.bar`, prefer optional chaining or type narrowing (warn level)
- **No accumulating spread** — don't use `{...acc, key: val}` inside `.reduce()`. Use a mutable object instead
- **No `delete` operator** — prefer destructuring or `Map`/`Set`

## When in Doubt

Run `pnpm biome check .` to validate. Run `pnpm biome check --write .` to auto-fix.
